==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[cran]]'', from Germanic ''[[*kran-]]'', from Proto-Indo-European ''[[*gerə-]]'' ("to cry hoarsely").

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪn|-eɪn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A large [[bird]] of the order ''[[Gruiformes]]'' and the family ''[[Gruidae]]'' having long legs and a long neck which it extends when flying.
# A [[mechanical]] [[lift]]ing [[device]], often used for lifing heavy loads for industrial or construction purposes.

